New Records: The Jazz set a season-high in points and Keyonte George tied his career high
Key Match Events: After Coby White tied the game, the Jazz outscored the Bulls 21-11 in the fourth quarter to pull away
Pre-Game Insights: The Jazz entered the game as the NBA's worst team offensively but performed well despite missing key players
Post-Match Reflections: The Bulls struggled without injured leading scorer Zach LaVine and the Jazz secured their first win of the season
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz shot 53.9% from the floor and 45.7% from three-point range; Collin Sexton added 24 points; Walker Kessler had 12 points and 15 rebounds
